TRXC for those that claimed my Post yesterday was FUD FACT TRXC must maintain 1 share price to keep its listing There is a process for delisting Trixie is listed on the NYSE market also called NYSE american exchange the old american so the requirements are more stringent I have attached basic articles describing the delisting process for both Ndaq and NYSE market Many funds CAN NOT HOLD delisted securities and are forced to sell BOTTOM LINE IS ALL I WAS SAYING IS IF THE STOCK TRADES BELOW 1 AND STAYS THERE FOR AN AMOUNT OF TIME it starts the clock which means the process for delisting begins It can take 6 months be appealed or a reverse split can be done but research shows reverse split companies rarely do well Trading 17 pennies away from this IS NOT A GOOD THING PERIOD investopediacomaskanswerfoolcomknowledgecenterd and for the advanced class wallstreetcchcomAmerican
